Kazakhstan's former president Nazarbayev issued a statement through his office on Saturday, calling on the nation to unite in support of the president to overcome the current challenges and ensure the integrity of the country. The statement said that Nazarbayev did not leave Kazakhstan but remained in the Nur-Sultan and was in touch directly with current president Tokayev, and also had telephone conversations with leaders from friendly countries. The statement called on the Kazakh public to remain calm and not listen to rumors.